# Agent routing (Cursor, Codex, human)

**Enforcement:** Follow this rule-set by default. To violate any rule below, stop and get **explicit per-action user approval** — name the rule being broken and the exact action. Do not infer override from vague task wording. One approval = one action.

**Default Dom:** Human for brand taste, merge/ship decisions, and secrets. Agents are Sub unless this doc assigns Dom.

## Role assignments

| Domain | Dom | Sub | Notes |
|--------|-----|-----|-------|
| Repo ship (edit, test, git, PR, MCP/SEO) | **Cursor** | Codex `exec` for review | Cursor owns ground truth in this monorepo |
| Raw codegen in existing codebase | **Cursor** | Codex on stuck/isolated logic | Match module-registry / tx-builder patterns first |
| Creative / complex assessment | **Codex** | Cursor to verify in tree | Audits, 10×, GTM critique, ambiguous tradeoffs |
| Greenfield architecture / spikes | **Codex** (draft) | **Cursor** (apply) | Codex must not commit; Cursor reconciles with branches |
| P0 security / non-custodial | **Cursor** implements | **Separate** reviewer Sub | Reviewer ≠ same thread that wrote the code |
| Social / marketing copy | **Cursor** orchestrator | Copywriter + SMM Subs; optional Codex pass | Log in `marketing/social/posting-log.md` |
| Brand / UX / Figma | **Human + Figma** | Agents | SVG/export/copy only — no AI-generated brand marks |
| Roadmap | **Codex draft → Cursor reconcile** | Human approves | Roadmap must match git reality (merged vs branch-only) |

## Codex invocation (Sub)

Use non-interactive exec from repo root when Sub role is assigned:

```powershell
codex exec -C "C:\Users\joshk\Token-Platform-Merged" -o .cursor/codex-last-output.md "<prompt>"
```

Prefer `-s workspace-write` only when Codex must edit files; default read-only review. Write output to a tracked path so Cursor Dom can merge findings.

CLI: `C:\Users\joshk\AppData\Local\OpenAI\Codex\bin\ea1c60319a1dcb19\codex.exe` (or `codex` on PATH).

## Cursor subagents (Sub under Cursor Dom)

| Subagent | Use |
|----------|-----|
| `explore` | Read-only repo discovery |
| `shell` | Git/CI commands |
| `bugbot` / `security-review` | Review only — user must ask |
| `composer-2.5-fast` | Parallel copy/drafts |

Cursor parent **synthesizes** Sub outputs; Subs do not ship conflicting changes without Dom merge.

## Hard rules (require explicit approval to break)

1. **Single Dom per branch/session** — never two agents both committing/editing the same branch without one orchestrator.
2. **No self-review on P0** — implementer and security reviewer must be separate passes (Codex `exec review` or dedicated review subagent).
3. **Codex Dom without Cursor apply** — architecture drafts may not land as commits until Cursor reconciles against the repo.
4. **No Codex for brand assets** — logos, marks, mocks stay SVG pipeline / Figma; agents supply copy and diagrams only.
5. **No silent `codex exec`** — tell the user when invoking Codex; show output path.
6. **Human Dom** — force-push, secret rotation, production env, and public Pjorg lore beyond deadpan social lines.

## When to escalate to human (never auto-override)

- Destructive git (force-push, history rewrite)
- `.env` / credentials / Stripe live keys
- Publishing npm, MCP registry, or social posts (deliver copy; user posts)
- Violating non-custodial positioning (memecoin hype, custodial flows)

## Override prompt template

Before breaking a rule, ask:

> This action would violate **\<rule N / name\>**: \<what you want to do\>. Approve this single override? (yes/no)

Proceed only on clear **yes** for that specific action.
